OL,6,FA therapist who said she had been
OL,7,Fdriven by Hopkinson before the
OL,8,Fincident, said: "This has affected him
OL,9,Fdeeply. He cannot remember the crash
OL,10,Fand cannot comprehend why he would
OL,11,Fdrive that way, especially with (his
OL,12,Fdaughter) in the car. It's mind
OL,13,Fboggling."JHopkinson was jailed for
OL,14,Feight years and banned from driving
OL,15,Ffor 12 years.
OL,17,FJudge Tom Bayliss KC told him: "You
OL,18,Fchose to drive at grossly excessive
OL,19,Fspeeds for some considerable distance.
OL,20,F"The speeds showed on the CCTV is
OL,21,Fbreathtaking."
